quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  12,7,In Joseph and his brothers there are certainly signs for the seekers
  12,8,"When they said, ‘Surely Joseph and his brother are dearer to our father than [the rest of] us, though we are a hardy band. Our father is indeed in manifest error.’"
  12,9,"‘Kill Joseph or cast him away into some [distant] land, so that your father’s attention may be exclusively towards you, and thereafter you may become a righteous lot.’"
  12,10,"One of them said, ‘Do not kill Joseph, but cast him into the recess of a well so that some caravan may pick him up, if you are to do [anything].’"
  12,11,"They said, ‘Father! Why is it that you do not trust us with Joseph? We are indeed his well-wishers"
  12,12,"Let him go with us tomorrow so that he may eat lots of fruits and play, and we will indeed take [good] care of him.’"
  12,13,"He said, ‘It really upsets me that you should take him away, and I fear the wolf may eat him while you are oblivious of him.’"
  12,14,"They said, ‘Should the wolf eat him while we are a hardy band, then we will indeed be losers!’"
  12,15,"So when they took him away and conspired to put him into the recess of a well, We revealed to him, ‘[A day will come when] you will surely inform them about this affair of theirs while they are not aware [of your identity].’"
  12,16,"In the evening, they came weeping to their father"
  12,17,"They said, ‘Father! We had gone racing and left Joseph with our things, whereat the wolf ate him. But you will not believe us even if we spoke truly.’"
  12,18,"And they produced sham blood on his shirt. He said, ‘No, your souls have made a matter seem decorous to you. Yet patience is graceful, and Allah is my resort against what you allege.’"
  12,19,"There came a caravan, and they sent their water-drawer, who let down his bucket. ‘Good news!’ he said. ‘This is a young boy!’ So they hid him as [a piece of] merchandise, and Allah knew best what they were doing"
  12,20,"And they sold him for a cheap price, a few dirhams, for they set small store by him"
  12,21,"The man from Egypt who had bought him said to his wife, ‘Give him an honourable place [in the household]. Maybe he will be useful to us, or we may adopt him as a son.’ Thus We established Joseph in the land and that We might teach him the interpretation of dreams. Allah has [full] command of His affairs, but most people do not know"
  12,22,"When he came of age, We gave him judgement and [sacred] knowledge, and thus do We reward the virtuous"
  12,23,"The woman in whose house he was, solicited him. She closed the doors and said, ‘Come!!’ He said, ‘God forbid! Indeed He is my Lord; He has given me a good abode. Indeed the wrongdoers are not felicitous.’"
  12,24,"She certainly made for him; and he would have made for her [too] had he not beheld the proof of his Lord. So it was, that We might turn away from him all evil and indecency. He was indeed one of Our dedicated servants"
  12,25,"They raced to the door, and she tore his shirt from behind, and they ran into her husband at the door. She said, ‘What is to be the requital of him who has evil intentions for your wife except imprisonment or a painful punishment?’"
  12,26,"He said, ‘It was she who solicited me.’ A witness of her own household testified [thus]: ‘If his shirt is torn from the front, she tells the truth and he lies"
  12,27,"But if his shirt is torn from behind, then she lies and he tells the truth.’"
  12,28,"So when he saw that his shirt was torn from behind, he said, ‘This is [a case] of you women’s guile! Your guile is indeed great"
  12,29,"Joseph, let this matter alone, and you, woman, plead for forgiveness for your sin, for you have indeed been erring.’"